summary: Reasons I love my dude
title: Reasons I love my dude
body:
The Dude (as he’s making coffee): But you know what REALLY bothers me?

Me (very absent-mindedly listening because yes, I am scrolling for new Endgame trailer content): what babe?

The Dude: The fact that no one talks about how Poe got all of those women killed in the space battle. You have all of these badass women and he got ALL of them killed because he wouldn’t listen to orders. It’s the only part of the movie I remember except for your lesbian hair person. It’s just not okay.

Me: I fucking love you.

summary: More Thrawn?
body:
More Thrawn?

I normally do not like imperials at all as they remind me of one of the darkest times of my country.

But I consider Thrawn more Chiss than imperial and therefore a rather interesting character.

On the one hand I constantly want to have more stories, series, comics, books etc… with him, but on the other hand I’m also quite scared to get too much information on him which might demystify him.

Does anyone have a similar dilemma?

summary: I read your Star Wars: A New Hope post and I wondered if you heard the Star Wars radio drama. It shows Leia torture "on screen"...
question: I read your Star Wars: A New Hope post and I wondered if you heard the Star Wars radio drama. It shows Leia torture "on screen" as it were and I was wondering if you had any thoughts
answer:
No, sorry I haven’t listened to it and the chances are I won’t.


I’m not Deaf but I do struggle a lot with processing sound so radio really isn’t my medium. Honestly I struggle to get through podcasts I really enjoy.


I’ve reviewed two episodes of a podcast before but- it took listening to the material quite a few times to actually take it in.


In this particular case I’d rather focus on reviewing all the Star Wars films then go into the expanded media. :)

Available on Wordpress.
